item.title: Project 1
item.description: #Data sets BodyMass<-read.csv("BodyMass.csv") Habitat<-read.csv("Habitat.csv") Introduction: The datasets I have chosen show the body mass and habitats of the world’s primates from a review of 1,216 published studies from 1941-2018. I have always been interested in primates and I am considering becoming a primatologist, so I thought this information would be interesting. Both datasets come from zenodo.org, which I found from the shared google sheet of datasets. Both datasets share the variables Family, Genus, CommonName, Species, and Species (ITIS), and the references used for the data.
